snippet.textDisplay: Dani, you are just so brave to be doing this. It's definitely a double-edged sword to be placed into such a high-profile group by virtue of being family and from the outside, Cimorelli really does seem to run like a well-oiled machine, an energizer bunny - just goes, goes, goes, goes, goes - millions of followers, billions of views, hundreds and hundreds of videos and songs, hundreds of performances, concerts for thousands of CimFam fans from all over the world for years. You lose sight of and appreciation for the hard work that goes into it. I'm sure it's way more than you or any of your sisters were expecting, hoping for, or even dreaming of when "Delaney was going to be a rock star." It can certainly get draining after a while and there's a lot of value in choosing your own goals and aspirations. I admire and respect the guts you showed in doing this and I know you'll be successful in whatever you do because you are bright, talented, and gifted. It was a privilege and an honor for me to see Cimorelli live 4 times (3 concerts and 1 meet & greet) in 2014, 2016,  and 2019 and there will be a missing element of the group without you. After all, if it weren't for you, we wouldn't have the gem, "Before October's Gone," the best Cimorelli original song ever written. I started following Cimorelli way back in 2011 when the CimFam EP with "Million Bucks" was about to be released "on December 6th." I've spent countless hours watching your videos, listening to your music, and singing your music in the shower and told many friends and family about how amazing you are and for that I thank you immensely. I even bought your "Up At Night" signed poster, which still hangs in my bedroom. You have truly made life worth living in the darkest times and shown me that I'm "Good Enough." You have a wide audience. I'm a male, soon to be 29 years old, living outside of Boston, MA, USA.

snippet.textDisplay: OK I didn’t really want to say this but now I have to. I love Cimorelli but to be honest they’re making this more dramatic than it has to be. They’re acting like they are never going to see her again when in reality they are still always going to be family so they’re still going to see her. She’s not dying, she’s not sick. She’s just leaving their group. She’s not leaving their family. This is different from a band who breaks up and they just know each other and aren’t family. Since Cimorelli is a family foremost this video shouldn’t be this dramatic. I love every single one of them and wish Danny wasn’t leaving so that we could still hear her voice in the group but things happen and growing up you discover you have different passions in life. She just doesn’t want to pursue music as her all and career. End of story there’s nothing more than that.

My honest opinion:
She started in the band when she was 9, a child and cimorelli has basecally been part of her childhood and teen years, just as for other people it might be going to school or doing dance classes 🤷🏼‍♀️... now she is 19 and she is in that period of life where you really start thinking about your future and what you are going to do. Her chosen career happend to not be a fulltime musician more a type of designer. Some of her sisters on the contrary, for example Cristina and Katherine started when they were already in their late teen years, just as Dani is now. So, just like her they started thinking what career and what they would like to do in the future and it happend to be musicians and start a band, just as someone decides to study medicine and be a doctor.
I hope my thoughts and ideas are somehow ant least kind of undersatndable...😅😅😅
